 '{"id":"sudoku_20260221","title":"The Archive''s Six Great Shelves","storyBeat":"The Archivist had six kinds of scrolls and six shelves â€” six rows, six columns, six tidy blocks. ''Every kind of scroll,'' he told young Hari, ''appears exactly once in each row, each column, and each block of six. Not a single scroll is ever doubled. Order, above all things.''","hint":"Chatur says: ''Work the 2Ã—3 blocks first â€” they give you the most constraints at once. Find a block where five kinds are already placed and the sixth writes itself in.''","winMessage":"Hari placed the last scroll perfectly. The Archivist ran his finger along every row and column without a word. Then: ''Correct.'' That was considered high praise.","grade":"4-7","category":"2.4","size":6,"digits":[1,2,3,4,5,6],"givens":[1,0,3,0,5,6,0,5,0,1,0,3,2,0,0,5,6,0,0,6,4,0,3,0,3,0,2,0,0,5,0,4,0,3,0,2],"solution":[1,2,3,4,5,6,4,5,6,1,2,3,2,3,1,5,6,4,5,6,4,2,3,1,3,1,2,6,4,5,6,4,5,3,1,2],"regions":[[0,1,2,6,7,8],[3,4,5,9,10,11],[12,13,14,18,19,20],[15,16,17,21,22,23],[24,25,26,30,31,32],[27,28,29,33,34,35]]}',
